title: "Non-determinism in LLM-as-Judge Graders: An Empirical Reproducibility Note"
type: report
authors:
  - family-names: "Tamba"
    given-names: "Hiroki"
    affiliation: "Tamba Research Academy"
    # orcid: "https://orcid.org/0000-0000-0000-0000"   # TODO: add real ORCID
version: "1.0"
date-released: "2026-06-07"   # TODO: update to the actual release date
license: CC-BY-4.0
url: "https://github.com/<your-account>/llm-judge-nondeterminism"   # TODO
abstract: >-
  LLM-as-judge graders are non-deterministic. A real evaluation harness
  (Japan AISI's aisev) calls its grader without controlling temperature or
  seed, so it runs unseeded at temperature 1.0 and near-boundary items flip
  pass/fail across runs. Even at temperature 0, a Claude grader still flips on
  2 of 7 items, showing temperature alone does not guarantee deterministic
  grading. The note gives a reproduction harness and concrete mitigations.
  Generalized from Japan-AISI/aisev issue #25.
keywords:
  - LLM-as-judge
  - model evaluation
  - reproducibility
  - non-determinism
  - AI safety evaluation
